I"û<h1 id="bash-parameter-expansion">Bash Parameter Expansion</h1>
<ul>
  <li>so today I learned there is a ternary like thing for bash.</li>
</ul>

<p>My old way of doing things</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>áš±@two-fer <span class="nv">$ </span>bat <span class="nt">-p</span> /tmp/stuff.sh
<span class="c">#!/bin/bash</span>

<span class="k">if</span> <span class="o">[</span> <span class="s2">"</span><span class="nv">$1</span><span class="s2">"</span> <span class="o">]</span>
<span class="k">then
    </span><span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s2">"One for </span><span class="nv">$1</span><span class="s2">, one for me."</span>
    <span class="nb">exit </span>0
<span class="k">fi

</span><span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s2">"One for you, one for me."</span>


áš±@two-fer <span class="nv">$ </span>
áš±@two-fer <span class="nv">$ </span>/tmp/stuff.sh 
One <span class="k">for </span>you, one <span class="k">for </span>me.
áš±@two-fer <span class="nv">$ </span>
áš±@two-fer <span class="nv">$ </span>/tmp/stuff.sh coolguy
One <span class="k">for </span>coolguy, one <span class="k">for </span>me.
áš±@two-fer <span class="nv">$ </span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Applying what I learnt!</p>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>áš±@two-fer <span class="nv">$ </span>bat <span class="nt">-p</span> /tmp/stuff.sh
<span class="c">#!/bin/bash</span>

<span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s2">"One for </span><span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">1</span><span class="k">:-</span><span class="nv">you</span><span class="k">}</span><span class="s2">, one for me."</span>

áš±@two-fer <span class="nv">$ </span>
áš±@two-fer <span class="nv">$ </span>/tmp/stuff.sh coolguy
One <span class="k">for </span>coolguy, one <span class="k">for </span>me.
áš±@two-fer <span class="nv">$ </span>
áš±@two-fer <span class="nv">$ </span>
áš±@two-fer <span class="nv">$ </span>/tmp/stuff.sh
One <span class="k">for </span>you, one <span class="k">for </span>me.
áš±@two-fer <span class="nv">$ </span>
</code></pre></div></div>
<ul>
  <li>The above example basically checks to see if the variable is set, if not, the default value will be used.</li>
</ul>
